headline: BAE Systems expands Utah footprint
summary: BAE Systems (LON: BA) announced the opening of its new office in Utah, marking an expansion of the company's local footprint and continued investment in the state's workforce, economy and innovation ecosystem.

headline: Maersk Air Cargo to cancel Asia-US flying with Boeing 767s, Amerijet
summary: Maersk Air Cargo is giving up on Boeing 767 freighters for trans-Pacific service and cutting ties with partner airline Amerijet as it transitions to the use of larger, more economical 777 jets. The post Maersk Air Cargo to cancel Asia-US flying with Boeing 767s, Amerijet appeared first on FreightWaves.
